    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-14T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-14T22:00:00-05:00" n="759"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d759">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">895.01/97: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-15T10:00:00+07:00"
                            >April 15, 1942—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 15—8:36 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>411. Department’s 283, April 11, 6 p.m. Action taken as directed. Vice Minister
                    has given assurances that Embassy will be kept currently informed of
                    developments and of Chinese Government’s views in regard to Korean question, and
                    that it will be notified in advance of any contemplated action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
